        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Extract embedded attachments (images, charts, OLE objects) from Excel (.xlsx) files via ZIP+OLE introspection. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  xlsx file attachment extraction: reads zip archive, locates media/embeddings in xl/ folder, parses OLE streams. \par \b Input\/ \:  File path to .xlsx document; optional parameters dict (with_attachments, need_content_analysis, attachments_dir). \par \b Output\/ \:  List of AttachedFile objects extracted from the xlsx archive. \par \b Links\/ \:  [USES_API(9): AbstractOfficeAttachmentsExtractor._get_attachments] \par \b Links\/ \:  [USES_API(8): recognized_extensions.excel_like_format, recognized_mimes.excel_like_format] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>extract ALWAYS returns a List[AttachedFile] (may be empty).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Parameters dict defaults to {} if None is passed. \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why delegate to _get_attachments with attachments_dir=&quot;xl&quot;? A: xlsx is an OpenXML format; the media folder resides under xl/ in the zip. The base class handles the zip iteration and OLE parsing generically. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 – Semantic markup + LDD logging added] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
<para>CLASS 8[Extracts attachments from .xlsx files] =&gt; ExcelAttachmentsExtractor METHOD 5[Constructor: registers recognized excel extensions/mimes] =&gt; <bold>init</bold> METHOD 8[Main extraction entry point for xlsx] =&gt; extract \par \b Use Cases\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>[extract]: DedocManager =&gt; ExtractXlsxAttachments =&gt; List[AttachedFile] </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
